# Bookshelf App Architecture Plan

## Overview
A full-stack Rust web application using Axum (backend) and Leptos CSR (frontend) with shared types.

## Workspace Structure
```
Cargo.toml          # workspace root
backend/
  Cargo.toml
  src/main.rs       # Axum server on 0.0.0.0:8080, serves API + static files
frontend/
  Cargo.toml
  src/main.rs       # Leptos 0.7+ CSR app entry point
  src/app.rs        # Root app component
  index.html        # Trunk entry HTML
  Trunk.toml        # Trunk config with /api/ proxy to backend
types/
  Cargo.toml
  src/lib.rs        # Shared types (serde Serialize/Deserialize)
```

## Key Design Decisions
- **Leptos CSR (client-side rendering)** via Trunk, not SSR — keeps frontend and backend cleanly separated
- **Trunk.toml** proxies `/api/` to `http://127.0.0.1:8080` during dev
- **Backend** uses `tower-http::services::ServeDir` to serve `frontend/dist` as fallback for production
- **types/** crate shared by both backend and frontend for API request/response types
- Backend binds `0.0.0.0:8080`

## Dependencies
- backend: axum, tokio, tower-http, serde, serde_json, types (path dep)
- frontend: leptos 0.7+, serde, serde_json, types (path dep), reqwasm/gloo-net for HTTP
- types: serde (with derive feature)

## Issue #1: Initialize Rust workspace
Sets up the entire scaffolding above with minimal hello-world endpoints and components.
No other issues exist yet — this is the foundation.
